THE SOPES are just about the most delicious thing I've ever had in my life. I always get 3: 2 carnitas and one shrimp. Their guac is good too. Their hot sauces are the best. We keep the extras to add to other foods. I speak Spanish so the language barrier isn't an issue, but I do have an issue with their POS system- they add up what you ordered in their head and charge you. They don't use a calculator or a computer/iPad. I have had a few problems with them adding incorrectly. Usually a few dollars off in my favor or theirs. But that's not enough to keep me from either popping in for sopes or having them delivered. I highly recommend you go in person if you don't speak Spanish because you will have a really hard time ordering on the phone. But do definitely try the sopes here they are amazing.
